I am a healthcare worker who has tried to support this restaurant with patronage for the past two years, especially after the pandemic. While the wings are great and majority of the staff wonderful, I have concerns over the owner. This place has good wings but questionable integrity.  A friend of mine visited the restaurant and was met with an uncomfortable and disappointing customer service situation. The owner was less than friendly and was disconcertingly rude to him in spite of being a frequent and reliable patron. Although he was disappointed, he wished to continue dining at the restaurant. However, when he attempted to dine at the restaurant after writing an honest review about his experience with the owner, he was told that he was banned. This schoolyard mentality and petty treatment of customers is unprofessional and disappointing at best. I wish I could say I would continue to frequent Blackbird for its delicious wings and otherwise lovely wait staff, but the owner has demonstrated a toxic treatment to her customers, and a mentality that is not conducive to the hopefulness and positivity of the times we live in today.
The staff is friendly, attentive and communicative especially during these times. The food was amazing as well as the drink specials.

After my friend’s review that stated our experience, we were not allowed to go back. The review was based on the rudeness of the owner (working as a waitress/bartender). Update: So my colleague and I who decided to visit back birds despite having a not so great experience as mentioned in the prior review was greeted at the door by the owner (female) who expressed her concern about my honest review. Instead of accepting the review from a customer's perspective on hospitality especially in a difficult time, the owner rightfully black listed my colleague and I from ever returning to black bird's. While this is the right of the owner to bar us (no pun intended) i truly believe that the owner has only showed her true colors with regards to how I felt from the prior experience. If customers are going to be banned from and entity because of an honest review with no disrespect I find it to be quite distasteful and unprofessional. It is during these difficult times that we try to support local businesses but when you are going to spend hard earned money at an entity with such behavior then it's safe to say that I too appreciate being barred from returning to black bird's. I really, really liked this place. Went here after work with my two friends. We got there at about 4:30. You can seat yourself wherever you want.  They have an extensive menu, many beer specials but I don't care for beer. The cocktails were $1 off during happy hour. They could do better with that. At least from 4-7 have a better happy hour price on cocktails.  The decor is beautiful! I felt like I was in a cabin in Maine I absolutely loved the quaint, cozy feel.  They have pub style tables a full bar and regular height tables. We chose a table at the back. They play lots of beatles music and that type of music. Service was very good as well. One of the girls doesn't drink and wanted coffee and the waitress brewed some just for her.  On to the food. It was really good.  I wasn't expecting it to be so good for bar food but it was really tasty, well prepared and everything came nout together & it was hot! We got mild wings,  steak tidbits on garlic toast,  nachos, mac & cheese and sweet potato fries.  Wings - cooked well, not too big, good flavor,crispy & nice portion size.  Sweet potato fries - crispy, salted with a side of aioli that was very good. I think out was chipotle flavored.  Nachos- crispy, cheese sauce with pickled jalapenos, black olives, tomato, lettuce & a side of sour cream and guacamole  (we got meatless)  Steak tid bits on garlic toast- steak was tender, cooked well with melted cheese on top & an au ju that was so flavorful it really made it come together.  Mac & Cheese- comes to the table in a cast iron skillet. The cheese sauce is rich,  creamy,  cheesy and seasoned just right.  Pasta is al dente and it's enough to share when you're sharing several things.  We got only one drink each. I can't remember the name, something hawaiian. It had vanilla vodka, pineapple juice and mint leaves. It was good but too small for $9 & didn't do a thing to me. Very weak.  I liked the place & I'd go back!

I’ll fill you in on some of the other parts of Blackbird’s Bar and Restaurant, but let’s be honest, you’re reading this because you saw deep fried grilled cheese in the title. Yes, it tastes just as good as it sounds.  Atmosphere  Blackbird’s is one of those neighborhood hangouts where it’s clear that mostly everyone knows everyone else, and the bartenders and waitstaff treat customers, both familiar and unfamiliar, as if they were part of their family. The bar/restaurant is rectangular shaped and outfitted in dark colors – reds and exposed brick – that complement a dark wood bar and tables.  Food  Here’s the part you’ve all been waiting for… deep fried grilled cheese! As soon as I saw this on the menu, I had to order it. You have the choice of adding bacon, tomato or avocado as well. I went with bacon. Since I already was going with a deep fried grilled cheese, I figured I might as well add to the artery clogging goodness.  The grilled cheese came out cut in half with a side of fries. The grilled cheese consisted of two very thick slices of white bread with lots of gooey American cheese and bacon in between. This was all lightly fried completely around. The frying locked in the flavor of the grilled cheese and kept the bread extremely soft. This sandwich was amazingly delicious. Oil from the frying oozed out during each bite and coated my fingers, only reaffirming my thought that my arteries were slowly clogging. After devouring this sandwich, I was stuffed. It’s very filling.  Service  Service at Blackbird’s is great. The waitstaff is extremely friendly and accommodating. I have no complaints.  Value  The deep fried grilled cheese was only about seven dollars. For an enormous grilled cheese and fries, this was one hell of a deal. An incredible value.  The Verdict  Blackbird’s is a quintessential neighborhood hangout and I could easily see myself heading here every Sunday for a few beers and some food. Kicking it up a notch is their deep fried grilled cheese. Twinkies, Oreos and now grilled cheese… you can deep fry anything. Blackbird’s is on the right path here. I’ve never seen this on a menu before and I can’t wait to come back and have it again. Blackbird’s, I’ll see you again very, very soon.
